/**
	 * <P>Poll the specified address for NTP service availability.</P>
	 *
	 * <P>During the poll an NTP request query packet is generated.
	 * The query is sent via UDP socket to the interface at the specified 
	 * port (by default UDP port 123).  If a response is received, it is 
	 * parsed and validated.  If the NTP was successful the service status 
	 * is set to SERVICE_AVAILABLE and the method returns.</P>
	 *
	 * @param iface		The network interface to test the service on.
